TextBlock.TextLine: take notice what you say as if I was the ouly agent of promotte
the makenny of cloathes here truly, in kent & others here before Jound
sonce other incamo to accuse mee, which sime hath showne themsence
the condrarie, non I finde makein, of cloth is the master indeed if
itt was not, that roosendael, kents heef correspondent here was the
onelj driver for itt, I must needs do soonething to, otheraise
our english trade shoud be muk less, for I lee make itt apeare that
sence I mads cloth hers I sold more english goods then before by
part for all the wollones that use to have of the mode culs, of thes
making, of n de mons come non to nice & to roosendael a by
their english goods what they shoud not do, had I not of my
fabrique, which I Jan sell for £4710 & ris finer spmnigh then
yd englusch of 14 a 15 ƒ8 a yd & yett the same qualitie of whole
batt 5 pray do not beleacce that makeing of cloth here undars mee
the lees able to carrie outhe English trade, soo I soock up no lesthen
£2000: to wards the fabrikes here, whick es have att a vere loce
rase p which iun lee borne vere well & much bester then bils att
2 uso was you for northren goods, as I could wish, I shoud affure
you to qve commissions for 120 a 130 bales m a yeare mall
& case you will examon every perticular, you will finde, that
what I do is to promose the englsh trade & to make ni megeson
univers to bester for you my selfe whilse I remaine
a 5 ged 1682
London A braham Vivian
on the 29 the last wrott to you the need full: sence rec yd of
21 the ditto which make mee yett more confues, because you tay
that the heary bayes vere not yett att ssale so I feare non shall
come whith snith, ys letter is full of slight arguments, which
makesnice beleave, that you have been altoghether back, in ordering
goods, when one shoud to have the been althoyether advantage oft
the marke: what signisyes to send goods to a marker when
the demand is hast you know I have of tendold you our aggresmer
with yd brother was, to past in £400- att least & more if the
trade doth reguire itt, that is £2000 each & pray make yd calcula
sion, if that mony be imployed for you & the trade beeng of greate
con feguence now then then ift was, soo wee want no less then
£2500 - aƒ 8 in case you shoud leave mee thus n blanco
Ishoud ee forced to take oher incasures, for a bove als I late to
be dirapointed in trade, where su wee dave advantidge, sot bays I must needs
have toof. of each vessel that coms from Hull, or elee I can do nothingl, I
save traded now 8 yeares, butt never in thes condition, I might have sold
3 a 4ooy more had I lad them, butt for you to drive trade of sull
a cousequence wishout a stock as there its reqused, is impon yett then
you must be plaine with mee & in no manner diapoint mee, tot I coud
be provided with the needfull, where now I hm much straigltned for
goods, & must see mij custemers desert mee, which I hope you ill take
considerabion, & compie with mij last desire of which I epe to know the
Iansicolars
london Jeage Cole Ben Loyd
C 5 dbre 1682
In answer to yd ouithout date of ang. lase, as for the 3 seales, I will make
some eminds in the parcell I am a preparing: ydt tykes I have not yet recd.
& for the future shall send ovely such as you shall desire, I cam promised them
nept week, when I lope to make up an assortment, Ioe which I shall putt
the mentioned laces well approving of yd proposite & sustrnction, which shall be
in all punctually observed, I returne you my thanckes for accepting my bill
please to observe that I have p for the laces I have by mee for you, & that I
shall make up the tykes, so that I am sure I shall not come short with the
bile I have drawne, yed pray excuse my boldness, itt was an appait the
ballance of an acctt
brugge Raphael coots
Antwerpen 9 gb 1682
Mons. in antwoort aen ul van ben 9 deser ten blijde dat ten iamin clarck
en ian henwick sijn gearriveert en volgens ul belofte soo hen de goederen
van inboort te gemoet alsoo om alles ben verlegen, ende noch meer om
de goederen bij ul te comen, de haelen sijn mij franc geworden waer voor
al bedancke, met tegenstaende dat ul hier sijnde hebt gelooft het op rechten
van de niewe mayasijn tot brussel niet te proteyeren soo worde echter
contrarie yenfor meert, terwijlen naer groetenisse blijve
Leuven Adriaen & veraerts
Adij 10 sber 1682
mons. alsoo ick moete eenigh gelt tot leuren hebben voor monst
Jean henrij gomes te betaelen soo hebbe aen hem een bewijshen
gegeven tot ul laste van een hondert entwintigh guldens segge ƒ120-
de welcke versoeke aen hem gelieft te betaelen en te stellen op ick van
amsterd Samuel de Haster
Adij 10 sber 1682
monsr. den ul van 20 passato en 3 deser wel ontfangen, ul traso
voldaen en vervolgens ul gedebiteert, het monster wol en wort bij ons
soo goet niet gevonden als die van tordelane, evenwel conde ul van de
selve 4 baelen coopen a 26½ soude du wel begeeren om my selven de
behelpen tot dat de verrachte schepen arriveren als wanneer perwat
avontuer de woll noch sal daelen en soo ƒ5 de sans van voorige
soorte hoch comt te ontfangen soude wel 20 a 12 baelen begeren
over sulckx gelieft daer over spicalaere te nemen en mij tadvisen
meuport Michiel de valleys
